-- Netherlands Beats Japan 1-0 for Second Straight Win at Soccer World Cup
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-19T13:19:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-19/netherlands-beats-japan-1-0-for-second-straight-win-at-soccer-world-cup.html

          
          
             The Netherlands beat Japan 1-0 for
its second straight victory at the World Cup in South Africa.  
 Wesley Sneijder scored in the 53rd minute in Durban for the
Netherlands, which tops Group E with six points.  
 Japan has three points, and Cameroon and Denmark have zero
going into their match tonight. Ghana plays Australia in Group D
in todayâ€™s other game.  
          
          


  


        